INSTALLATION:

First install the following dependencies:

-Python 2.4 or later(http://www.python.org)
-PyQt 4.x (http://www.riverbankcomputing.co.uk/software/pyqt/download)
-If you want to be able to enter formulas using latex syntax, make sure that
 latex is installed.
-Type 'python setup.py install' as root.
-Run the application by typing 'mnemosyne'.


HACKING ON MNEMOSYNE:

If you want to contribute to mnemosyne or want to make any local changes, you
will additionally need the following tools:

-Qt-Designer: Useful to modify the .ui xml-files.
-pyuic: required to convert the .ui files to python code.

If you check out the source from CVS, you have to install it by typing 
'make' rather than 'python setup.py install'
